getElementByClassName():
returns all the elements having the same class name

example:
<h1 id="a" class="a"> I am meghana</h1>
<h2 id="b" class="b"> I am naavs</h2>
<h1 id="c" class="a"> I am nandu</h1>

<script>
    let a = document.getElementsByClassName('a'); // Correct method name
    console.log(a);

    for(let i = 0; i < a.length; i++) { // Use 'a' instead of 'x'
        console.log(a[i]);
    }


getElementByClassId():
returns an html collection object
An html collection is an array like list of html elements
